1 The legislature declares that establishing a biliteracy
2 program within the university of Hawaii is a matter of statewide
3 concern pursuant to article X, section 6, of the Hawaii State
4 Constitution.
5 Accordingly, the purpose of this Act is to establish a
6 program within the university of Hawaii that enables eligible
7 high school graduates who have earned the seal of biliteracy and
8 community members with demonstrated biliteracy competency to be
9 recognized as qualified translators and interpreters,
10 SECTION 2. Chapter 304A, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
11 amended by adding a new section to part IV, subpart M, to be
12 appropriately designated and to read as follows:
13 "§304A- Language access education and workforce
14 development program; established. (a) There is established
15 within the university of Hawaii the language access education
16 and workforce development program.
17 (b) The language access education and workforce
18 development program shall be administered by the university of
19 Hawaii SEED office in collaboration with academic departments on
20 all campuses, the department of education, the department of
