1 labor and industrial relations, and other relevant public and
2 private entities.
3 (c) The language access education and workforce
4 development program shall provide a curriculum for training
5 eligible participants to be recognized as qualified translators
6 and interpreters. The curriculum shall include:
7 (1) Training in translation and interpretation, including
8 ethics, standards, and best practices;
9 (2) Specialized instruction and opportunities for
10 interpretation in public service settings, including
11 settings related to education, health care, social
12 services, legal services, agriculture, and government
13 services; and
14 (3) A certificate of completion of program requirements
15 for qualified translation and interpretation
16 proficiency;
17 provided that participants shall complete educational
18 requirements, including internship opportunities through the
19 hele imua program of the department of labor and industrial
20 relations; provided further that the program shall include
