1 (d) Priority for admission to the language access
2 education and workforce development program shall be given to
3 applicants who have earned the seal of biliteracy issued by the
4 department of education. All other applicants to the language
5 access education and workforce development program shall
6 demonstrate, as a requirement of admission, proficiency in
7 English and at least one additional language, as determined by
8 program standards or by obtaining the Global Seal of Biliteracy
9 credential."
10 SECTION 3. There is appropriated out of the general
11 revenues of the State of Hawaii the sum of $375,000 or so much
12 thereof as may be necessary for fiscal year 2026-2027 to carry
13 out the purposes of this Act, to be allocated as follows:
14 (1) $225,000 for the establishment of three full-time
15 equivalent (3.0 FTE) positions; provided that Leeward
16 community college, Kapiolani community college, and
17 the university of Hawaii at Manoa shall each host one
18 position; and
19 (2) $150,000 to implement the language access education
20 and workforce development program; provided that the
21 funds shall be divided equally between Leeward
